
A:
	How are you doing today? I haven't seen you in a while.

B:
	What are they?

A:
	I marvel thou didst send him from thee----

B:
	[Indignantly.] And yet--you hesitate! Why, this is the greatest
thing of its kind ever attempted! There are unprecedented
possibilities! A whole new world of knowledge may be opened up--the
very origin of Man himself! And you will be the only woman--

A:
	Really? Now that's hard to believe. 

B:
	I studied at the academy, your honour, and pursued my studies in
Eberswalde. Shortly before the final examinations I met with this
misfortune....

A:
	I certainly am making a dupe of no one--

B:
	And what then? She put an end to that long ago. You
have had her letters, so you know this yourself.

A:
	It's all about finding the balance.

B:
	Well, did you catch him?

A:
	You are quite right, Lady Caroline.

B:
	They've got things like that there, too?

A:
	That is surprising - I never thought about it like that before.

B:
	I! Nothing.

A:
	Oh, dear! Have you forgotten where you live?

B:
	Thank you, dear!
